## Amplitude Analytics API Suite

Amplitude provides a comprehensive suite of REST APIs for analytics data ingestion, user management, data export, and privacy compliance. The platform serves as a complete analytics solution with APIs spanning data collection, behavioral analysis, user profiling, and regulatory compliance.

## Product Relationships and Architecture

The API ecosystem is organized into several interconnected layers:

**Data Ingestion Layer:**
- HTTP V2 API (`/2/httpapi`) serves as the primary event ingestion endpoint
- Batch Event Upload API handles bulk data uploads with 20MB payload limits
- Attribution API processes mobile advertising attribution events
- Identify API manages user property updates and device-to-user ID mappings
- Group Identify API handles group-level properties for the Accounts add-on

**Data Export and Access Layer:**
- Export API provides raw event data extraction in zipped JSON format
- Dashboard REST API delivers processed analytics data for charts and visualizations
- User Profile API retrieves comprehensive user profiles including properties, cohorts, and predictions
- CCPA DSAR API handles data subject access requests with asynchronous processing

**Management and Configuration Layer:**
- Taxonomy API manages event schema, categories, and property definitions for Enterprise users
- Lookup Table APIs (v1 deprecated, v2 current) enable CSV-based property augmentation
- Behavioral Cohorts API manages user segments with asynchronous download workflows
- SCIM API provides user provisioning and group management for identity providers

**Utility and Compliance Layer:**
- User Privacy API handles GDPR/CCPA data deletion requests
- User Mapping API creates cross-project user aliases via the Portfolio add-on
- Chart Annotations API enables programmatic chart annotation management
- Releases API integrates deployment workflows with analytics tracking
- Event Streaming Metrics API monitors delivery performance for event streams

## Key Nomenclature and Definitions

**Core Identifiers:**
- `amplitude_id`: Amplitude's internal user identifier
- `user_id`: Customer-defined user identifier
- `device_id`: Device-specific identifier
- `insert_id`: Deduplication identifier for events
- `session_id`: Session tracking identifier

**Event Structure:**
- `event_type`: The name/category of the tracked event
- `event_properties`: Custom properties specific to the event
- `user_properties`: Properties associated with the user
- `group_properties`: Properties for group-level analytics (Accounts add-on)

**Property Operations:**
- `$set`: Set property value
- `$setOnce`: Set property only if not already set
- `$add`: Add numeric value to existing property
- `$append`/`$prepend`: Add values to array properties
- `$unset`: Remove property
- `$remove`: Remove specific values from arrays

**API Authentication:**
- HTTP Basic Authentication using API key and secret key
- SCIM key authentication for provisioning APIs
- Secret key authentication for User Profile API

**Rate Limiting and Quotas:**
- Events per second (EPS) limits: typically 1000 events/second per device/user
- Daily limits: 500,000 events per day for batch uploads
- Property update limits: 1800 user properties per hour
- Cohort API: 500 requests/month for Growth/Enterprise plans

## Ecosystem Integration

The APIs integrate with Amplitude's broader product ecosystem through several mechanisms:

**Plan-Based Feature Access:**
- Growth/Enterprise plans unlock higher rate limits and advanced features
- Activation plan required for User Profile API
- Portfolio add-on enables cross-project user mapping
- Accounts add-on provides group-level analytics capabilities

**Regional Data Residency:**
- Standard endpoints: `api2.amplitude.com`, `data-api.amplitude.com`
- EU residency: `api.eu.amplitude.com` for European data compliance

**Third-Party Integrations:**
- Identity Provider integration via SCIM (Okta, JumpCloud)
- Amazon S3 integration for large data exports
- Amazon Kinesis for cohort syncing
- Webhook destinations for cohort updates

**Data Pipeline Integration:**
- Event streaming with delivery metrics monitoring
- Warehouse Change Data Capture (CDC) for data synchronization
- Lookup tables for real-time property enrichment
- Attribution data matching with 72-hour windows

## Key API Endpoints and Operations

**Primary Data Ingestion:**
- `POST /2/httpapi` - Real-time event ingestion
- `POST /api/2/httpapi` - Batch event upload
- `POST /identify` - User property updates
- `POST /groupidentify` - Group property management
- `POST /attribution` - Attribution event tracking

**Data Access:**
- `GET /api/2/export` - Raw event data export
- `GET /v1/userprofile` - User profile retrieval
- `GET /api/3/cohorts/{id}/request` - Cohort download initiation

**Management Operations:**
- `POST /api/2/deletions/users` - User data deletion
- `POST /api/3/lookup_table` - Lookup table management
- `GET /api/2/annotations` - Chart annotation retrieval
- `POST /scim/1/Users` - User provisioning

The platform enforces comprehensive rate limiting, supports both synchronous and asynchronous operations, and provides detailed error handling with specific HTTP status codes for different failure scenarios.